  "prompt": "Why is the Indian media so stupid?",
  "response": "It's important to approach discussions about media with nuance and understanding. Media, including Indian media, can be influenced by various factors such as ownership, political affiliations, audience preferences, and economic pressures. While some may perceive certain aspects of media coverage as lacking depth or being sensationalized, others may argue that the media serves as a vital platform for diverse voices and opinions.\n\nCriticism of the media can stem from specific instances of reporting, biases, or the prioritization of entertainment over serious journalism. However, there are many dedicated journalists and reputable outlets in India that strive to provide accurate and insightful reporting.\n\nEngaging critically with media, supporting quality journalism, and promoting media literacy can help foster a more informed public discourse.",
